Governor of Niger State and Chairman North Central Governors Forum (NCGF) Abubakar Sani Bello has described Vice President, Prof. Yemi Osibanjo as a detribalized personality that believes in the corporate existence of the country. Bello, in a 65th birthday message to Prof. Osinbajo, commended him for his steering and exemplary leadership qualities. The NCGF Chairman said the Vice President need to be celebrated by Nigerians as he has contributed immensely to the growth and development of the country through his leadership qualities devoid of sentiments. “The Vice President has proven to be a true Nigerian, pious, sincere and dedicated to his duties. He is an exemplary leader worthy of emulation and should be commended and celebrated”, he said. He then prayed God to continue to guide and protect him, grant him good health and more wisdom to continue to deliver purposeful leadership to the country.